{PLAGUE BURIAL GROUNDS}
In the middle ages Leith was hit by many plagues. The worst plague it was hit by was the Black Death. Folk got it from the rats that came off the ships and then went down into the drains and tunnels and that's where it spread. They would probably get into your house and contaminate the food. There was no cure for it in those days.So that folk knew you had the plague you would draw a red cross on your door. A man would come round and shout,"Bring out your dead!" There are some plague victims' burial grounds along at the eastern end of Seafield on Leith Links.
.
